<Paragraph Margin="0,0" FontSize="12" Foreground="silver">Interestingly, the spyglass actually has a slightly different effect depending on what field-of-view (FOV) your game is set to on the options screen. By default, Java edition has a FOV of 70Â° and Bedrock edition has a slightly-more-zoomed-in FOV of 60Â°, but that can be changed to whatever you want. Whatever itâ€™s set to, a spyglass will give you a tenth of it, creating a zoom effect.</Paragraph>
